# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Names of the infra / third-party secrets Harmonic expects — REFERENCE ONLY.
#
# This is a contract, not a store. Harmonic is open source and deployed by many
# operators, so NO secret material — plaintext or ciphertext — ever lives in
# this repo. Each value is bring-your-own and stays private to your deployment.
#
# To supply the file-mounted ones, materialize one file per name under
# $SECRETS_DIR (default `secrets/run/`, gitignored), which the compose
# `secrets:` overlay mounts to /run/secrets/<NAME>. Two supported ways:
#
#   1. Pre-place the files yourself (scp, config-mgmt, your password manager's
#      CLI). This is the default; scripts/deploy.sh needs no hook.
#   2. Install a populate hook that fetches from your private source at deploy
#      time. See secrets/adapters/ for example hooks (SOPS+age, AWS SSM, Vault).
#
# When the overlay is enabled, EVERY file-mounted name below must have a file
# (compose errors on a missing source). Leave a file EMPTY to keep that secret
# on the legacy .env path — the initializer ignores empty files.
#
# One file per NAME; the file's contents are the value.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- File-mounted today (read after initializers; see the overlay) ----------

# DigitalOcean Spaces secret key (ActiveStorage) — from `terraform output`
DO_SPACES_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY

# Stripe (billing + AI gateway)
STRIPE_API_KEY
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET

# OAuth
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET

# Cloudflare Turnstile (bot protection; blank disables verification)
TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY

# Agent-runner shared secret — file-mounted for the Rails side only; the
# agent-runner service itself still gets it from .env (compose-interpolated)
AGENT_RUNNER_SECRET

# --- NOT file-mountable yet (keep in .env on the server) --------------------
#
# Read before initializers run (config/environments/production.rb or
# database.yml ERB), or interpolated by compose itself — the /run/secrets
# initializer fires too late for these. Moving them requires a container
# entrypoint export; see "Boot-ordering caveat" in docs/INFRASTRUCTURE.md.
#
#   POSTGRES_PASSWORD (and POSTGRES_HOST/PORT/DB/USER)  — database.yml ERB
#   SMTP_PASSWORD (and SMTP_* settings)                 — production.rb, pre-init
#   REDIS_PASSWORD / REDIS_URL                          — compose-interpolated +
#                                                         production.rb, pre-init
#
# App-internal secrets (SECRET_KEY_BASE, and AGENT_RUNNER_SECRET long-term)
# belong in Rails encrypted credentials (config/credentials.yml.enc) —
# different owner, blast radius, and rotation cadence.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Non-secret settings (Spaces region/bucket/endpoint, SMTP username, Stripe
# publishable/gateway keys, Sentry DSN, etc.) are plain configuration and stay
# in the environment / compose config, not here.
